FORMAT: 1A
HOST: https://api.example.com

# Task Management API

A comprehensive API for managing tasks, projects, developers, and notifications.

# Group Tasks

## Tasks Collection [/tasks{?status,assignee,project,priority,limit,offset}]

### List all tasks [GET]
+ Parameters
    + status: open (string, optional) - Filter by task status
    + assignee: dev123 (string, optional) - Filter by assigned developer ID
    + project: proj456 (string, optional) - Filter by project ID
    + priority: high (string, optional) - Filter by priority level
    + limit: 50 (number, optional) - Maximum number of results
    + offset: 0 (number, optional) - Pagination offset

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[Task])

### Create a task [POST]
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (TaskCreate)

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Task)

## Task Detail [/tasks/{taskId}]
+ Parameters
    + taskId: task789 (string, required) - The unique task identifier

### Get task details [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Task)

### Update a task [PATCH]
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (TaskUpdate)

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Task)

### Delete a task [DELETE]
+ Response 204

## Task Comments [/tasks/{taskId}/comments]
+ Parameters
    + taskId: task789 (string, required) - The unique task identifier

### List task comments [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[Comment])

### Add a comment [POST]
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (CommentCreate)

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Comment)

# Group Projects

## Projects Collection [/projects{?status,owner,limit,offset}]

### List all projects [GET]
+ Parameters
    + status: active (string, optional) - Filter by project status
    + owner: dev123 (string, optional) - Filter by project owner ID
    + limit: 50 (number, optional) - Maximum number of results
    + offset: 0 (number, optional) - Pagination offset

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[Project])

### Create a project [POST]
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (ProjectCreate)

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Project)

## Project Detail [/projects/{projectId}]
+ Parameters
    + projectId: proj456 (string, required) - The unique project identifier

### Get project details [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Project)

### Update a project [PATCH]
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (ProjectUpdate)

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Project)

### Delete a project [DELETE]
